<title>USA: Electronic Retailing says in label deal.</title>
<headline>Electronic Retailing says in label deal.</headline>
<dateline>WILTON, Conn. 1997-05-06</dateline>
<text>
<p>Electronic Retailing Systems International Inc said Tuesday it signed a letter of intent with Sweda Canada Inc to market its wireless electronic shelf labels and software in Canada.</p>
<p>The company said it does not yet know the potential dollar value of the deal.</p>
<p>Electronic Retaiing said its shelf label system eliminates the need for paper price tags by allowing pricing information to be automatically changed when prices in a special scanner is changed.</p>
